Class GVREyePointee

  • java.lang.Object

  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    GVRMeshCollider
    Deprecated. 
    use GVRCollider

    public class GVREyePointee
extends GVRCollider
    Super class of GVRMeshEyePointee. An GVREyePointee is something that is being pointed at by a picking ray. GVREyePointees are held by eye pointee holders. Eye pointee holders are attached to GVRSceneObjects so they can be returned by the GVRPicker.

    This bizarre little class only contains a constructor and was intended as a sort of interface. The only actual GVREyePointee is GVRMeshEyePointee.
